A 28-year-old man has been charged with murder after a Latvian man was found dead in a flat in Scotland.
The body of Aleksandrs Sokolovs, 29, was discovered in a property in Tummel Road, Glenrothes, Fife, last Monday.
Police Scotland said that a man is due to appear at Kirkcaldy Sheriff Court tomorrow.
In a statement issued through police today, the family of Mr Sokolovs said: &quot;Aleksandrs was a very friendly person who loved to travel and experience different cultures.
&quot;He was a loving son and brother, and will be missed by all persons who knew him.&quot;
